For a positive integer $n,$ the factorial notation $n!$ represents the product of the integers\\
from $n$ to $1.$ (For example, $6! = 6 \cdot 5 \cdot 4 \cdot 3 \cdot 2 \cdot 1.$) What value of $N$ satisfies the following equation?\\
$$5! \cdot 9! = 12 \cdot N!$$$\textbf{(A) }10 \qquad \textbf{(B) }11 \qquad \textbf{(C) }12 \qquad \textbf{(D) }13 \qquad \textbf{(E) }14$
